ner.<ref name=\"BMX_0412\"/> \n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat2}}\" | EF2\n|NW of [[Summerville, Georgia|Summerville]] to SE of [[LaFayette, Georgia|LaFayette]]\n|[[Chattooga County, Georgia|Chattooga]], [[Walker County, Georgia|Walker]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.4990|-85.3689|name=Summerville (Apr 12, EF2)}}\n|00:15\u201300:32\n|{{convert|15.8|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|800|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A {{convert|10,000|lb|kg|abbr=on}} camper was overturned. Shingles and siding were pulled off homes. A trailer was destroyed, a corner of a barn's exterior wall was heavily damaged, and numerous large trees were snapped or uprooted. Toward the end of the tornado's path, it ripped the roof and entire second story off a house, causing severe damage to its exterior walls. A jeep was tossed more than {{convert|150|yd|m|abbr=on}}. Another nearby home had its garage collapsed and a large portion of its roof removed.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\">{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Peachtree City, Georgia |title=NWS Damage Survey for 04/12-13/2020 Tornado Event|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSFFC&e=202004222119|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet |date=April 22, 2020 |accessdate=April 22, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|[[Carbon Hill, Alabama|Carbon Hill]]\n|[[Walker County, Alabama|Walker]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|33.8795|-87.5472|name=Carbon Hill (Apr 12, EF1)}}\n|01:12\u201301:16\n|{{convert|2.9|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|1000|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A site-built home had sections of its roofing ripped off, and various residential and professional buildings in Carbon Hill suffered damage. At least five manufactured homes and outbuildings were either rolled or demolished, shifted off their block piers, or sustained significant loss of roof and walls. Dozens of trees were snapped or uprooted. Three people were injured.<ref name=\"BMX_04