 of [[Higdon, Alabama|Higdon, AL]] to S of [[Trenton, Georgia|Trenton, GA]]\n|[[DeKalb County, Alabama|Dekalb (AL)]], [[Dade County, Georgia|Dade (GA)]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.8349|-85.6120|name=Higdon (Apr 12, EF1)}}\n|02:50\u201303:05\n|{{convert|7.55|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|350|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A tornado damaged large sections of the Shiloh Community Church and damaged a barn. Minor structural damage occurred on mobile homes and trees were snapped.<ref name=\"0412HUN\" /> The tornado continued into Georgia where it damaged nearly 100 homes in and around the city of Trenton.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|ESE of [[Heiberger, Alabama|Heiberger]]\n|[[Perry County, Alabama|Perry]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|32.7317|-87.2012|name=Heiberger (Apr 12, EF1)}}\n|03:14\u201303:18\n|{{convert|2.42|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|350|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n| A church had its roof torn off and a nearby building was destroyed. Extensive tree damage occurred along the tornado's path.<ref name=\"BMX_0412\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat3}}\" | EF3\n|[[Fort Oglethorpe, Georgia|Fort Oglethorpe, GA]] to NE of [[Ooltewah, Tennessee|Ooltewah, TN]]\n|[[Catoosa County, Georgia|Catoosa (GA)]], [[Hamilton County, Tennessee|Hamilton (TN)]], [[Bradley County, Tennessee|Bradley (TN)]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]], [[Tennessee|TN]]\n|{{Coord|34.9407|-85.2582|name=Fort Oglethorpe (Apr 12, EF3)}}\n|03:15\u201303:33\n|{{convert|20|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|1500|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|3 deaths \u2013 A tornado touched down near [[Chickamauga and Chattanooga National Military Park]], south of [[Chattanooga, Tennessee|Chattanooga]], and traveled northeast. The tornado impacted an industrial area on the south side of Fort Oglethorpe, damaging multiple businesses. A weather station at the Public Works Department measured an unconfirmed gust of {{convert|106|mph|km/h|abbr=on}}. Thereafter, the tornado produced weak, sporadic tree and structural damage through before intensifying as it moved into Tennessee.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/> Extensive damaged occurred in the Harris Hills neighborhood where an auto-parts store was leveled and several structures had severe roof damage. Widespread damage continued into the Drake Forest neighborhood, Ooltewah, and the Integra Hills Preserve Apartments where many homes sustained roof damage. The tornado ultimately dissipated in southwestern Bradley County.<ref name=\"EastChatupdate\">{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Morristown, Tennessee |title=NWS Damage Survey for 04/12/2020 Tornado Event Update #2|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSMRX&e=202004181853|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet |date=April 18, 2020 |accessdate=April 18, 2020}}</ref> At least 150 structures were damaged or destroyed, 3 people were killed, and 19 people were injured.<ref name=\"tn\">{{cite web |title=Update: NWS: \"At least an EF3\" tornado struck Chattanooga Sunday night, 10 dead in area |url=https://newschannel9.com/news/local/severe-weather-causes-major-local-damage-late-sunday-night |publisher=WTCV |date=April 13, 2020 |accessdate=April 13, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|NE of [[Collinsville, Alabama|Collinsville]]\n|[[DeKalb County, Alabama|DeKalb]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|34.2744|-85.8560|name=Collinsville (Apr 12, EF0)}}\n|03:22\u201303:28\n|{{convert|3.56|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|110|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Several trees were downed, and a small barn was destroyed.<ref name=\"0412HUN\" />\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|SE of [[Sardis, Alabama|Sardis]] to S of [[Tyler, Alabama|Tyler]]\n|[[Dallas County, Alabama|Dallas]]\n|[[Alabama|AL]]\n|{{Coord|32.2440|-86.9515|name=Belnap (Apr 12, EF0)}}\n|03:27\u201303:31\n|{{convert|3.8|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|400|y