 Fujita scale|EF#]]\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:7%; text-align:center;\" class=\"unsortable\"|Location\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\" class=\"unsortable\"|County / Parish\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:5%; text-align:center;\"|State\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Start Coord.\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Time ([[Coordinated Universal Time|UTC]])\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Path length\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Max width\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:48%; text-align:center;\"|Summary\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|WNW of [[Cave Spring, Georgia|Cave Spring]]\n|[[Floyd County, Georgia|Floyd]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.1239|-85.3675|name=Cave Spring (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|04:31\u201304:32\n|{{convert|0.5|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Several trees were downed and large tree limbs were broken off by a brief tornado.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|N of [[Lindale, Georgia|Lindale]] to W of [[Rome, Georgia|Rome]]\n|[[Floyd County, Georgia|Floyd]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.1924|-85.1735|name=Lindale (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|04:42\u201304:45\n|{{convert|3.2|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n| A brief tornado downed multiple trees, some of which fell on power lines.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|WSW of [[Cartersville, Georgia|Cartersville]] to E of [[White, Georgia|White]]\n|[[Bartow County, Georgia|Bartow]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.1492|-84.82855|name=Cartersville (Apr 13, EF1)}}\n|05:06\u201305:21\n|{{convert|13|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|250|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|1 death \u2013 A tornado touched down west-southwest of Cartersville and caused minor damage to a small business and downed fences. In southwestern Cartersville, a large oak tree fell on a house, killing the sleeping occupant. Sporadic tree damage continued thereafter until it reached Bells Ferry Road where numerous trees were snapped or uprooted and one home was damaged. The tornado continued into the Pine Log Wildlife Management Area where 60\u201370 trees were downed before it dissipated. Two people were injured along its path.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|SSW of [[Salacoa Valley, Georgia|Salacoa Valley]]\n|[[Cherokee County, Georgia|Cherokee]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.3524|-84.6028|name=Salacoa Valley (Apr 13, EF1)}}\n|05:32\u201305:33\n|{{convert|0.71|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|100|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|This tornado regenerated from the 05:06&nbsp;UTC Bartow County tornado. Around 250 to 300 trees were downed northwest of [[Waleska, Georgia|Waleska]].<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|NW of [[Waverly Hall, Georgia|Waverly Hall]]\n|[[Harris County, Georgia|Harris]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|32.7279|-84.7294|name=Waverly Hall (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|05:53\u201305:55\n|{{convert|3|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Several trees in a remote and forested area were downed.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|NW of [[Woodland, Georgia|Woodland]]\n|[[Talbot County, Georgia|Talbot]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|32.7516|-84.5144|name=Woodland (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|06:08\u201306:10\n|{{convert|2.9|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|100|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Trees downed by the tornado blocked several roads.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat3}}\" | EF3\n|S of [[Thomaston, Georgia|Thomaston]] to NW of [[Redbone, Georgia|Redbone]]\n|[[Upson County, Georgia|Upson]], [[Lamar County, Georgia|Lamar]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|32.8496|-84.3335|name=Thomaston (Apr 13, EF3)}}\n|06:19\u201306:35\n|{{convert|16.7|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|1200|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A tornado touched down just south of Thomaston and traveled northeast. It steadily intensified and grew in diameter as it approached Trice Cemetery Road. There, a mobile home was rolled and rotated 90\u00b0. Farther northeast, one home had the majority of its roof torn off and nearly all trees within {{convert|220|yd|m|abbr=on}} of it were snapped. The National Weather Service's WSR-88D radar detected debris lofted up to {{convert|25000|ft|m|abbr=on}} at this time. Thereafter, the tornado weakened and ultimately dissipated shortly after crossing into Lamar County. A total of 159&nbsp;structures were affected by the tornado; 7 were destroyed, 20 had major damage, and 38 had minor damage.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|NNE of [[Union City, Georgia|Union City]]\n|[[Fulton County, Georgia|Fulton]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|33.6288|-84.5263|name=Union City (Apr 13, EF0)}}\n|06:36\u201306:39\n|{{convert|2.75|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|50|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A short-lived tornado snapped or uprooted many trees; debris was detected by the local NWS's radar up to {{convert|1000|ft|m|abbr=on}}.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat3}}\" | EF3\n|SW of [[Collier, Georgia|Collier]] to NNW of [[Forsyth, Georgia|Forsyth]]\n|[[Monroe County, Georgia|Monroe]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|33.0928|-84.033|name=Forsyth (Apr 13, EF3)}}\n|06:40\u201306:47\n|{{convert|5.3|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|300|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|This tornado regenerated from the 06:19&nbsp;UTC Upson/Lamar County tornado. The tornado initially touched down southwest of Collier and quickly intensified as it approached Highway 41. There, a large metal building and small home were completely destroyed. The metal frame and concrete footers of the former structure were ripped from the ground, leaving behind a concrete slab. The occupant of the small home was injured. Several vehicles, a small plane, a tractor, and a boat were flipped near the structures. NWS radar detected debris up to {{convert|19000|ft|m|abbr=on}}. Continuing northeast, the tornado caused extensive tree damage as it gradually weakened, ultimately dissipating near Highway 42.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|W of [[Raoul, Georgia|Raoul]] to SSW of [[Boydville, Georgia|Boydville]]\n|[[Hall County, Georgia|Hall]], [[Habersham County, Georgia|Habersham]], [[Banks County, Georgia|Banks]], [[Stephens County, Georgia|Stephens]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|34.456|-83.6449|name=Raoul (Apr 13, EF1)}}\n|06:50\u201307:03\n|{{convert|14.38|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|200|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|Numerous trees were snapped or uprooted and one mobile home sustained minor to moderate roof damage.<ref name=\"FFC_0415\"/><ref>{{cite report|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Greenville-Spartanburg, South Carolina |title=NWS Damage Survey for Habersham and Stephens County Georgia EF1 Tornado Event|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSGSP&e=202004162027 |publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet |date=April 16, 2020 |accessdate=April 16, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|SW of [[Collier, Georgia|Collier]] to NNW of [[Forsyth, Georgia|Forsyth]]\n|[[Bibb County, Georgia|Bibb]]\n|[[Georgia (U.S. state)|GA]]\n|{{Coord|32.873|-83.7718|name=Collier (Apr 13, EF1)}}\n|07:00\u201307:04\n|{{convert|3.7|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|300|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A short-lived tornado touched down near [[Interstate 475 (Georgia)|Interstate 475]], causing minor roof damage to two hotels and a [[Walmart]]. A nearby [[Walgreens]] had all of its windows blown out and a hole punctured into its roof. A gas station canopy ha