ent|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSSHV&e=202004210023|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat1}}\" | EF1\n|N of [[Leesville, Louisiana|Leesville]]\n|[[Vernon Parish, Louisiana|Vernon]]\n|[[Louisiana|LA]]\n|{{Coord|31.1666|-93.3313|name=Leesville (Apr. 19, EF1)}}\n|21:50\u201321:57\n|{{convert|5.4|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|500|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|An EF1 tornado snapped, uprooted, or downed numerous trees and power lines. Some of those trees fell on homes and vehicles.<ref>{{cite web|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Lake Charles, Louisiana|title=NWS Damage Survey for 04/19/20 Tornado Event|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSLCH&e=202004201948|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|cat4}}\" | EF4\n|ESE of [[Tylertown, Mississippi|Tylertown]] to NW of [[New Augusta, Mississippi|New Augusta]]\n|[[Walthall County, Mississippi|Walthall]], [[Marion County, Mississippi|Marion]], [[Lamar County, Mississippi|Lamar]], [[Forrest County, Mississippi|Forrest]], [[Perry County, Mississippi|Perry]]\n|[[Mississippi|MS]]\n|{{Coord|31.0716|-89.9644|name=Marion County (Apr. 19, EF4)}}\n|00:10\u201301:19\n|{{convert|54.2|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|2200|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|1 death \u2013 A long-tracked, massive, and violent tornado destroyed multiple mobile homes, causing one fatality, and severely damaged additional houses. One home was completely demolished and had its anchor bolts bent. A higher rating was not assigned because debris remained on the home's foundation. Severe damage was inflicted to a church and the nearby pastor's home, and behind his house, a {{convert|40|ft|m|abbr=on}} shed was destroyed and blown a few feet away. Several headstones in a cemetery were knocked over. Multiple wooden