railer across the roadway. It then snapped numerous trees, and caused mainly minor roof and window damage along an intermittent path.<ref>{{cite web|agency=National Weather Service Weather Forecast Office in Jacksonville, Florida|title=NWS Damage Survey for Marion County 4/20 Tornado|url=https://mesonet.agron.iastate.edu/wx/afos/p.php?pil=PNSJAX&e=202004201835|publisher=Iowa Environmental Mesonet|date=April 20, 2020|accessdate=April 20, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|storm}}\" | EF0\n|[[Lake Jesup]]\n|[[Seminole County, Florida|Seminole]]\n|[[Florida|FL]]\n|{{Coord|28.7186|-81.2418|name=Lake Jesup (Apr. 20, EF0)}}\n|15:45\u201315:48\n|{{convert|2.75|mi|km|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|{{convert|25|yd|m|abbr=on|sortable=on}}\n|A waterspout moved across Lake Jesup to the east of [[Winter Springs, Florida|Winter Springs]].<ref>https://apps.dat.noaa.gov/StormDamage/DamageViewer/</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n===April 22 event===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|+ List of reported tornadoes \u2013 Wednesday, April 22, 2020{{efn|All dates are based on the local [[time zone]] where the tornado touched down; however, all times are in [[Coordinated Universal Time]] for consistency.|group=note|name=Date/Time}}\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:3%; text-align:center;\"|[[Enhanced Fujita scale|EF#]]\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:7%; text-align:center;\" class=\"unsortable\"|Location\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\" class=\"unsortable\"|County / Parish\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:5%; text-align:center;\"|State\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Start Coord.\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Time ([[Coordinated Universal Time|UTC]])\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Path length\n! scope=\"col\"  style=\"width:6%; text-align:center;\"|Max width\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:48%; text-align:center;\"|Summary\n|-\n|bgcolor=\"{{storm colour|unk}}\" |